{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:32:18.898227+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "---\n\n## Summary: Create React App Firebase Starter — Install, Configure & Deploy\n\nThis repository (`rpnr-bench/T02_R02`) is a **Create React App (CRA) custom template** that bundles React, Firebase (with Google Sign-In), Material UI, React Router, and GitHub Pages deployment out of the box. Here's how to use it end-to-end.\n\n---\n\n### 1. Installation\n\nUse the CRA template system with the `firebase-starter` template name:\n\n```bash\nnpx create-react-app your-project-name --template firebase-starter\n# or\nyarn create react-app your-project-name --template firebase-starter\n```\n\nThis scaffolds a new project with all dependencies pre-installed, including:\n- **React 18**, **React Router v6**, **Firebase v9**, **Material UI v5**, and **gh-pages** (dev dependency).\n\nA TypeScript variant also exists at `cra-template-typescript-firebase`.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Firebase Configuration\n\nThe template expects all Firebase credentials via **environment variables** in a `.env` file at the project root. The file `template/.env` ships with placeholder values:\n\n```\nREACT_APP_FirebaseApiKey=<your-key>\nREACT_APP_FirebaseAuthDomain=<your-domain>\nREACT_APP_FirebaseProjectId=<your-project-id>\nREACT_APP_FirebaseStorageBucket=<your-bucket>\nREACT_APP_FirebaseMessagingSenderId=<your-sender-id>\nREACT_APP_FirebaseAppId=<your-app-id>\n```\n\n**Steps:**\n\n1. Go to the [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com/) → **Add project** → follow the prompts.\n2. Click the **web icon** (</>) → Register a web app → copy the `firebaseConfig` object it gives you.\n3. Paste the values into your `.env` file, mapping each field to the corresponding `REACT_APP_Firebase*` variable.\n4. In **Firebase Console → Authentication → Sign-in method**, enable **Google** sign-in.\n\nThe config is read at runtime by `src/config/firebase.config.js`, which pulls directly from `process.env.REACT_APP_Firebase*`. The actual Firebase app initialization lives in `src/config/firebase.js`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Adding New Screens\n\nRoutes are declared in `src/config/routes.js`. Each entry has the shape:\n\n```js\n{\n  path: \"/your-route\",\n  component: YourScreenComponentName,\n  name: \"Screen Name For Reference\",\n  protected: false,   // true = only authenticated users can access\n}\n```\n\nCreate new screen components in `src/screens/` and register them here. The template includes `AuthChecker` and `AuthContainer` components (`src/components/auth/`) for gating protected routes.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Deploying to GitHub Pages\n\nThe template uses the `gh-pages` npm package and the `spa-github-pages` library for client-side routing support on GitHub Pages.\n\n**Steps:**\n\n1. **Whitelist your domain in Firebase:**  \n   Go to **Firebase Console → Authentication → Sign-in method → Authorized domains** and add `your-github-username.github.io`.\n\n2. **Update `homepage` in `package.json`:**  \n   Change it to your GitHub Pages URL:\n   ```json\n   \"homepage\": \"https://your-github-username.github.io/your-repo-name\"\n   ```\n\n3. **(Optional) Test the production build locally:**  \n   Temporarily set `\"homepage\": \"/\"` in `package.json`, then:\n   ```bash\n   npm i -g serve          # one-time global install of `serve`\n   npm run build-and-serve  # builds and serves the static output\n   ```\n\n4. **Deploy:**\n   ```bash\n   npm run deploy\n   ```\n   This runs `npm run build` (via the `predeploy` hook) followed by `gh-pages -d build`, which pushes the `build/` folder to the `gh-pages` branch. Your site will be live at the `homepage` URL.\n\n---\n\n### Key Scripts Reference\n\n| Script | What it does |\n|---|---|\n| `npm start` | Local dev server (`react-scripts start`) |\n| `npm run build` | Production build (`react-scripts build`) |\n| `npm run build-and-serve` | Build + serve locally with `serve -s build` |\n| `npm run deploy` | Build & deploy to GitHub Pages via `gh-pages` |", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 967, "prompt_tokens": 11552, "total_tokens": 12519, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 33, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 11328, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0003338384, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 6.30784e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00027076}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780871524-Dbt1taHgO8FO1Cliov5h", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea436-ee49-7203-a238-e5d074bcdc89-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 11552, "output_tokens": 967, "total_tokens": 12519, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 11328}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 33}}}}]}}}
